# Architecture Guardrails

These rules enforce production-portable patterns. After editing any file in `src/modules/`, run `npm run lint:arch && npm run lint:boundaries` and fix any violations before moving on.

---

## Mandatory Skill Gates

Before taking any of these actions, complete the associated checklist:

| Action | Checklist |
|--------|-----------|
| Creating a new component under `src/modules/` | Follow the "New Component Checklist" below |
| Editing `.html`, `.css`, `.js` in `src/modules/` | Follow the "UI Code Checklist" in `slds-rules.mdc` |
| Editing `cosmos-theme.css`, `cosmosApp.css`, or `cosmos-brand-*.css` | Follow the "Theme CSS Rules" below |
| Adding a new page or nav item | Follow the "New Page Checklist" below |

---

## Namespace Rules

All components live in `src/modules/` under exactly one of these namespaces:

| Namespace | Tag Prefix | Can import from | Cannot import from |
|-----------|------------|-----------------|-------------------|
| `shell/` | `shell-*` | `data/`, `ui/`, `src/router.js` | `page/` |
| `page/` | `page-*` | `data/`, `ui/` | `shell/`, other `page/` |
| `ui/` | `ui-*` | `data/labels/`, other `ui/` | `page/`, `shell/`, `data/*` (except labels) |
| `data/` | (import only) | other `data/` | `shell/`, `page/`, `ui/` |

Never create components outside these four namespaces.

---

## i18n-Ready Label Pattern

**No hardcoded user-facing strings in templates.** All text in `title`, `label`, `placeholder`, `alternative-text`, and `aria-label` attributes must come from label modules.

**Pattern:**

```javascript
// src/modules/data/labels/MyFeature.js
export const PageTitle = 'My Feature';
export const SearchPlaceholder = 'Search...';
```

```javascript
// Component JS
import { PageTitle, SearchPlaceholder } from 'data/labels/MyFeature';
export default class PageMyFeature extends LightningElement {
    labels = { PageTitle, SearchPlaceholder };
}
```

```html
<!-- Template -->
<lightning-card title={labels.PageTitle}>
<lightning-input placeholder={labels.SearchPlaceholder}>
```

**Rules:**
- One file per page or feature area (`Home.js`, `Contacts.js`)
- Shared labels ("Cancel", "Save", "Close") go in `Common.js`
- This mirrors `@salesforce/label/` — porting to core is a path swap

---

## Theme CSS Rules

Two files, strict separation:

| File | Owns | Never put here |
|------|------|----------------|
| `public/cosmos-theme.css` | All visual styling: backgrounds, borders, backdrop-filter, gradients, colors, glass treatments | position, z-index, width, height, padding, margin, display, flex, grid |
| `src/modules/shell/cosmosApp/cosmosApp.css` | Layout only: positioning, z-index, dimensions, padding, transforms, transitions, `--cosmos-*` properties | background, backdrop-filter, border-color, box-shadow, color, fill, stroke |

**Why:** `cosmos-theme.css` is global and crosses synthetic shadow boundaries. `cosmosApp.css` is scoped to the host — visual properties placed here silently fail to reach child components.

