## New Component Checklist

1. Determine the correct namespace (`page/` for routes, `ui/` for reusable, `shell/` for app chrome, `data/` for JS-only)
2. Create `src/modules/<namespace>/<componentName>/<componentName>.{html,js}`
3. Create a label file at `src/modules/data/labels/<ComponentName>.js` for all user-facing strings
4. If `page/`: add route to `src/routes.config.js` and register in `shell/app/app.js` `ROUTE_COMPONENTS`
5. Run `npm run lint:arch && npm run lint:boundaries`

---

## New Page Checklist

1. Create `src/modules/page/<pageName>/<pageName>.{html,js,css}`
2. Create `src/modules/data/labels/<PageName>.js` with all user-facing strings
3. Add route entry to `src/routes.config.js`:
   ```javascript
   {
     path: '/<page-name>',
     component: 'page-<pageName>',
     title: '<Page Title>',
     navPage: '<page-name>',
     navLabel: '<Nav Label>',
   }
   ```
4. Import and register the component in `src/modules/shell/app/app.js` under `ROUTE_COMPONENTS`
5. If it should appear in nav: add entry in `shell/globalNavigation` or `shell/verticalNav`
6. Run `npm run lint:arch && npm run lint:boundaries`

---

## After Every Edit

After modifying any file in `src/modules/` or `public/`:

1. Run `npm run lint:arch` — fix any blocking violations (namespace), address warnings (labels, CSS)
2. Run `npm run lint:boundaries` — fix any import boundary violations
3. Verify the dev server still renders correctly at `http://localhost:4360`
